1311:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****       (#) In System clock config, HSI48 needs to be enabled
1312:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c **** 
1313:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****       (#) Enable CRS clock in IP MSP init which will use CRS functions
1314:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c **** 
1315:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****       (#) Call CRS functions as follows:
1316:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****           (##) Prepare synchronization configuration necessary for HSI48 calibration
1317:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****               (+++) Default values can be set for frequency Error Measurement (reload and error lim
1318:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****                         and also HSI48 oscillator smooth trimming.
1319:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****               (+++) Macro __HAL_RCC_CRS_RELOADVALUE_CALCULATE can be also used to calculate
1320:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****                         directly reload value with target and synchronization frequencies values
1321:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****           (##) Call function HAL_RCCEx_CRSConfig which
1322:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****               (+++) Resets CRS registers to their default values.
1323:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****               (+++) Configures CRS registers with synchronization configuration
1324:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****               (+++) Enables automatic calibration and frequency error counter feature
1325:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****            Note: When using USB LPM (Link Power Management) and the device is in Sleep mode, the
1326:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****            periodic USB SOF will not be generated by the host. No SYNC signal will therefore be
1327:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****            provided to the CRS to calibrate the HSI48 on the run. To guarantee the required clock
1328:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****            precision after waking up from Sleep mode, the LSE or reference clock on the GPIOs
1329:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****            should be used as SYNC signal.
1330:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c **** 
1331:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****           (##) A polling function is provided to wait for complete synchronization
1332:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****               (+++) Call function HAL_RCCEx_CRSWaitSynchronization()
1333:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****               (+++) According to CRS status, user can decide to adjust again the calibration or con
1334:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****                         application if synchronization is OK
1335:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c **** 
1336:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****       (#) User can retrieve information related to synchronization in calling function
1337:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****             HAL_RCCEx_CRSGetSynchronizationInfo()
1338:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c **** 
1339:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****       (#) Regarding synchronization status and synchronization information, user can try a new cali
1340:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****            in changing synchronization configuration and call again HAL_RCCEx_CRSConfig.
1341:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****            Note: When the SYNC event is detected during the downcounting phase (before reaching the
1342:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****            it means that the actual frequency is lower than the target (and so, that the TRIM value
1343:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****            incremented), while when it is detected during the upcounting phase it means that the ac
1344:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****            is higher (and that the TRIM value should be decremented).
